<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Holocaust memorial -- An Oct. 29 report about President Clinton's visit to Yad 
Vashem, the Israeli Holocaust memorial, incorrectly identified a Polish Jewish 
educator honored for sheltering Jewish orphans during World War II.Janusz 
Korczak died at the Treblinka death camp with 200 of his charges, after they 
were deported from the Warsaw ghetto. Korczak turned down a last-minute offer 
of freedom, choosing instead to stay with the children and board the cattle 
cars taking them to Treblinka. A statue in his honor stands at Yad Vashem. 
</P>
