<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; COUGAR QUARTERBACK PREPPED STRONGLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Washington State's sophomore quarterback, Chad Davis, at one time held the 
national high school career passing yardage record. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis, who played at three high schools -- Palm Springs, Del Mar Torrey Pines 
and San Diego Mira Mesa -- passed for 9,332 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis, who transferred from Oklahoma to Washington State after one year, has 
started every game this season and is a 57% passer with nine touchdown passes. 
</P>
<P>
 USC plays at Washington State on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 USC has another injury at guard. Freshman starter Chris Brymer sprained an 
ankle during pregame warm-ups for the Cal game two weeks ago and might not be 
on the plane when USC leaves today for Pullman.  
</P>
<P>
 Previously, Clay Hattabaugh and Phalen Pounds were sidelined after knee 
surgery. Kris Pollack and Kyle Ramsay are expected to start at guard Saturday.  
</P>
<P>
 Also, junior linebacker Errick Herrin has a thigh bruise that has kept him out 
of practice and his status for Saturday is uncertain. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
