WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; CAR-PROTECTION SHEETS AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Camarillo residents may pick up plastic sheets Saturday to protect their cars 
from aerial pesticide spraying aimed at wiping out the Mediterranean fruit fly. 
</P>
<P>
 The car covers will be available in the parking lot of Camarillo City Hall, 
601 Carmen Drive, from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. The sheets are being distributed by 
the Ventura County Fruitfly Action Cooperative Taskforce, a group of local 
growers and packinghouse officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The next aerial spraying is scheduled for Wednesday evening. It will cover the 
same 16-square-mile area that was sprinkled earlier with a sticky mixture of 
malathion and bait. 
</P>
<P>
 The sprayings are scheduled to continue for at least six months, until the 
86-square-mile quarantine is lifted. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents in the spray zone are encouraged to reuse their car covers. If they 
cannot pick up car covers, sheets may be used to protect the paint finish. 
JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
