<P>
 An 18-year-old Ventura woman was killed and another teen-ager seriously 
injured in a head-on collision Thursday when their car crossed the center 
stripe on a narrow stretch of Telegraph Road in Saticoy, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Elizabeth Ann Aguilar was dead at the scene, authorities said.Firefighters had 
to cut the roof off the 1967 Chevrolet to extricate three others, including two 
toddlers, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the car, Ventura resident Serena Lopez, also 18, was in serious 
condition at Ventura County Medical Center after undergoing surgery for a 
broken leg, police and hospital officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez's two young daughters, who were wearing seat belts but were not in 
safety seats, escaped the crash without serious injury, although one girl had a 
broken arm, said Ventura Police Cpl. John Turner. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that they saw Lopez's car swerving in the eastbound lane 
of Telegraph Road near Saticoy Avenue shortly before noon. Her car crossed the 
double yellow line and slammed into a 1988 Buick, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of that car, Thomas Davis, 59, of Ventura was not seriously 
injured, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez did not have a license with her, and Turner said he was investigating 
the accident to determine if Lopez was driving recklessly. He said alcohol use 
apparently was not a problem. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez told investigators that car trouble caused her to swerve out of control, 
Turner said. MATTHEW MOSK 
