<TEXT>
<P>
 New York Probes Lloyd's Trust: The New York Insurance Department is 
investigating whether troubled Lloyd's of London can meet its claims-paying 
responsibilities to U.S. insurers. A team from the department spent several 
weeks in London combing financial records at Lloyd's American Trust Funds to 
determine whether they have enough money to pay potential claims. The trust is 
similar to a guarantee fund that backs U.S. insurers that use Lloyd's as a 
safety net in case of excessive claims from commercial and property insurance 
policyholders. 
