GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; VAQUEROS STOP LATE CHARGE BY SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos got 196 rushing yards from senior Chris Young, but Vaquero 
fans had to hold their breath until the end of Thursday's 13-12 victory over 
Santiago at Bolsa Grande High. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos (6-2-1, 5-0) led, 13-6, at halftime on the strength of two 
long drives, but the Cavaliers (3-6, 2-3) made their runs at the league-leading 
Vaqueros in the final quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Santiago drove inside the Vaquero 20 early in the fourth quarter, but had 
to settle for a 29-yard field-goal attempt. The kick by Jose Palacios, who had 
made only one field goal this season, was wide right. 
</P>
<P>
 -- On the ensuing Rancho Alamitos possession, the Cavaliers appeared to hold 
when a pass on third and nine at the Cavalier 39 fell incomplete. However, a 
facemask penalty against Santiago resulted in a first down at the Santiago 25. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Santiago took over at its 20 with 2 minutes 52 seconds remaining after the 
Vaqueros missed a 31-yard field-goal attempt. Two running plays were good for a 
first down, and then senior Anthony Callari broke loose for a 48-yard run, 
before fumbling at the Rancho Alamitos 20. Mike Ogle recovered, and Rancho 
Alamitos ran out the clock. 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago used a variety of backs to grind out 229 rushing yards. Callari 
finished with 94 yards. ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</TEXT>
