<HEADLINE>
<P>
EMPIRE LEAGUE; KIRKLAND LEADS LOARA PAST CYPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loara quarterback Jim Kirkland threw for 186 yards and one touchdown and ran 
for another score to lead the Saxons to a 28-6 Empire League victory over 
Cypress Thursday night at Glover Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saxons (4-5, 3-1) scored three fourth-quarter touchdowns.They moved into a 
tie for first place with El Dorado and Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
 In a scoreless first half, Cypress managed only 37 yards of total offense. 
</P>
<P>
 Loara scored quickly in the second half. A 68-yard pass from Kirkland to 
Dalbert Rodriguez on the second play of the third quarter set up Kerry Peoples' 
two-yard touchdown run with 10 minutes 20 seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing 7-0, the Centurions (2-7, 0-4) battled back on their next possession. 
Bobby Brito's two-yard run capped a six-play drive, making the score 7-6. 
</P>
<P>
 After a Loara touchdown pass was called back because of a holding penalty, the 
Saxons scored four plays later on a two-yard run by Kirkland. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saxons struck again on their next possession when Kirkland found Aaron 
Beverly on a 14-yard touchdown pass, giving Loara a 21-6 lead with 5:53 
remaining. JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
