<HEADLINE>
<P>
CENTURY LEAGUE FOOTBALL; VILLA PARK DEFENSE TOPS CANYON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Villa Park's 14-10 victory over Canyon featured a hard-hitting defense, which 
held the Comanches to minus-25 yards rushing, and wide receiver Sean Adams, who 
caught five passes for 107 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Those were the on-field highlights. 
</P>
<P>
 However, there were plenty of strange sights off the field in Thursday's 
Century League football game at El Modena High. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon wide receiver Greg Jacobs, who led the county in receptions heading 
into this week, warmed up with his teammates in uniform, but watched the game 
in street clothes because of an ankle injury he suffered last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park's Franklin Haynes, the team's leading rusher who gained 198 yards 
in a 14-0 victory over Orange last week, also did not play. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's suspended," Villa Park Coach Pat Mahoney said. "It's a school matter." 
Mahoney wouldn't further comment on the matter. 
</P>
<P>
 Mahoney's counterpart, Canyon Coach Bob Hughes, watched the game from the 
stands behind the Canyon bench. He was suspended for two games by Century 
League officials. 
</P>
<P>
 Still, Canyon (6-3, 2-2 in league) played well defensively, forcing three 
turnovers. The Comanches held Villa Park (8-1, 3-1) to 29 yards rushing in the 
first half. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Canyon offense sputtered, although quarterback Adam Hoover completed 
16 of 25 passes for 210 yards. Hoover connected with Tim Tynan for a 32-yard 
touchdown pass to put Canyon ahead, 10-7, with 5 minutes remaining in the third 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But Villa Park's Sam Bell and Chris Stremick each intercepted one pass and the 
Spartans sacked Hoover five times. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park quarterback Sean McMahon, who completed 12 of 19 passes for 177 
yards with one interception, tossed a 28-yard touchdown pass to Adams with 27 
seconds remaining in the second quarter to give the Spartans a 7-3 halftime 
lead.  
</P>
<P>
 Adams caught a 13-yard touchdown pass with 30 seconds remaining in the third 
quarter to give Villa Park a 14-10 lead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
