</P>
<P>
 In the all-Laguna Beach doubles final, Lindsey Weiss and Amanda 
Hastings-Phillips defeated Sarah Cohen and Vanessa Zajfen, 6-4, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison pair wins -- Edison doubles players Tami Demaree and Susie Krum 
defeated Michelle Schneider and Alison Miller of Los Alamitos, 6-1, 7-5 in the 
final. 
</P>
<P>
 In Century League girls' volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 3, El Modena 0 -- Tenth-ranked Orange (16-0, 10-0) defeated third-place 
El Modena (6-4), 15-6, 15-9, 16-14. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 3, Cypress 1 -- Katella (12-4, 9-1) earned share of its first league 
title with a 1-15, 15-9, 15-6, 15-0 victory over third-place Cypress (6-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 3, Buena Park 0 -- Eighth-ranked La Habra (13-1, 9-1) finished tied 
for the league title with Sunny Hills by winning 15-3, 15-5, 15-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills 3, Sonora 0 -- Christie Blunt had seven aces to lead No. 4 Sunny 
Hills (15-1, 9-1) to a 15-1, 15-3, 16-14 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 3, Western 0 -- La Quinta Alexander, Carrie Ritchey and Michelle 
Shear each had seven kills to lead Valencia (13-3, 10-0), 15-6, 15-6, 15-2. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 3, El Toro 2 -- Kelly Campbell had 20 kills and Kathryn Rice 19 
to lead second-place Corona del Mar (8-6, 8-2) to a 15-13, 13-15, 14-16, 15-13, 
15-5 victory over third-place El Toro (5-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 3, Capistrano Valley 0 -- Abigail Daniels had 12 kills to lead 
ninth-ranked Mater Dei (14-4, 8-2) to a 16-14, 15-7, 15-2 victory. The Monarchs 
finish second in league; Capistrano Valley (5-5) third. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 3, Marina 2 -- Second-ranked Edison (15-1, 9-1) won the league title 
with a 15-10, 15-8, 11-15, 9-15, 15-1 victory over Marina (5-5), which finished 
tied with Esperanza for third. Esperanza will receive the automatic playoff 
spot. 
</P>
<P>
 In South Coast league water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 16, Mission Viejo 6 -- Andy Bailey and Jordon Hewko each had five 
goals for San Clemente as the Tritons (22-2, 5-0) defeated Mission Viejo and 
win their eighth South Coast League title in 14 years. 
</P>
