<P>
PREP CROSS-COUNTRY ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICHARD MELKONIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Aliso Niguel girls' win first league title -- Jenny Speirs' third-place finish 
at Irvine Regional Park in Orange helped Aliso Niguel win its first league 
title in girls' cross-country. 
</P>
<P>
 Speirs, who finished in 19:36, was one of five Wolverine runners who finished 
among the top 10.Aliso Niguel finished with 28 points, Laguna Hills was second 
with 63 and University was third with 75. 
</P>
<P>
 Aliso Niguel's league victory is the first for the school in any sport since 
it opened last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Mandy Schwercherl of Laguna Hills and sophomore Misha Wilson of 
University battled until the final 500 meters when Schwercherl pulled away to 
win in 18:29. Wilson finished in 18:54. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills won the boys' title with the help of strong finishes by Danny 
Minx, who finished second in 16:00, and Allan Kremp, who took third in 16:50. 
University's Richard Chou finished first in 15:57. RICHARD MELKONIAN 
</P>
