COLLEGE ROUNDUP; SOTO SCORES THREE, SETS TITAN RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eddie Soto scored three goals and set a school record Thursday night as Cal 
State Fullerton defeated California 5-2 in nonconference men's soccer at Titan 
Field. 
</P>
<P>
 With his third goal of the night, Soto set the Fullerton record for most goals 
scored in a career with 36. Soto broke the record of Mike Fox, who now plays 
for the Salsa. 
