<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; HART BOYS STRETCH CROSS-COUNTRY TITLE STREAK TO 12 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The names change from year to year, but the results continue to be the same 
for the Hart High boys' cross-country team, which won its 12th consecutive 
championship in the Foothill League finals at College of the Canyons on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Paced by the 1-2-3 finish of senior Brett Strahan and juniors John Duarte and 
Joel Givens, the Indians placed five runners among the top seven finishers to 
total 18 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank, led by fourth-place Kevin Harley, finished second with 67 points, 
followed by Saugus (69), Canyon (85) and Burroughs (136). 
</P>
<P>
 Strahan, the runner-up in last year's Southern Section Division I 
championships, timed 15 minutes 46 seconds over the three-mile course to win 
his second consecutive league title. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon, paced by individual winner Julie Harris, won the girls' competition to 
tie Hart for the league title. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart had defeated Canyon in the first two league meets -- which counted toward 
50% of the league title -- this season, but Canyon placed four runners among 
the top seven finishers to post a 27-46 victory over the Indians. Defending 
league champion Saugus was third with 59, followed by Burbank (104) and 
Burroughs (142). 
</P>
<P>
 Harris, a sophomore competing in her first season of cross-country, timed 
19:44 to turn back Saugus sophomore Breanne Schweitzer (19:49), winner of the 
first two league meets. JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</TEXT>
