<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORTHY OPENS SEASON ON INJURED LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Lakers reached the 12-man roster limit Thursday by putting James Worthy on 
the injured list and, in a surprise move, cutting rookie point guard Trevor 
Ruffin. 
</P>
<P>
 Worthy sat out the final three exhibition games and several practices after 
returning to North Carolina for his mother's funeral, and the Lakers did not 
think he would be in basketball shape to open the season.When the announcement 
was made, however, they said the veteran small forward would sit out at least 
five games because of tendinitis in his left knee. 
</P>
<P>
 The decision to waive Ruffin was unexpected, because Executive Vice President 
Jerry West had been so high on the free agent from Hawaii, the find of summer 
league play at UC Irvine. It also means that both Antonio Harvey and Anthony 
Miller have made the team, giving the Lakers six power forwards and centers. 
SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
</TEXT>
