<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; CUBA; U.S. COURT OVERTURNS RULING ON REFUGEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cuban refugees at the U.S. naval base at Guantanamo Bay and in Panama can be 
returned to their homeland pending arguments on an order that blocked their 
repatriation, an appeals court ruled. The 11th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in 
Atlanta overturned a lower court's order, thereby allowing the government to 
begin returning the more than 30,000 Cuban refugees held at Guantanamo Bay and 
in Panama. Arguments in the case are scheduled for this afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
