<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Beach is trying to break into show business. 
</P>
<P>
 The city is forming a film committee and is looking for residents interested 
in helping to get more television shows and movies shot in the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee, to be composed of seven to 15 members, will initially review 
the current film-permitting process and develop marketing strategies. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials hope the committee will make the entertainment industry more 
aware of locations suitable for filming in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 536-5553. Today 
</P>
<P>
 An open house for a new exhibit on World War II begins at 7 p.m. at the Los 
Alamitos Historical Museum, 11062 Los Alamitos Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 At 7:30 p.m., World War II veteran Richard Hedricks will discuss the B-17 
bomber, known 
</P>
<P>
 as the Flying Fortress, which he flew during the war. 
</P>
<P>
 He will also discuss the surrender of Sardinia, in which he participated.  
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 431-8865 or (310) 431-5306. 
