<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Equestrian Center and children from George Washington 
Elementary School in Burbank will hold a tree-planting ceremony at 2 p.m. Nov. 
25 at the center. 
</P>
<P>
 About 20 third- and fifth-graders will plant native trees in a field at the 
center at 480 Riverside Drive to replace those removed because of disease. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will commemorate the Equestrian Center's ongoing support of an 
environmental science park on the George Washington campus. 
</P>
