 The park was built last year and is in the second phase of construction. It 
currently houses facilities that show students how to grow organic vegetables, 
herbs, flowers and fruit. 
</P>
<P>
 Future developments for the park include a greenhouse and man-made rain 
forest. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Equestrian Center is deeply rooted in the Burbank community," said Jana 
Olson Collins, equestrian center spokeswoman. "This is the school's way to show 
its appreciation." ALICIA DOYLE 
