<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LA PALMA; RENTAL FEES ESTABLISHED FOR NEW PARK FACILITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has enacted fees for individuals and businesses who want to 
reserve the new Plaza Pavilion area at Central Park for private events and 
parties. 
</P>
<P>
 By a unanimous vote, the council decided that residents who reserve the 
pavilion will be charged $30 an hour.Businesses and corporations will be billed 
$45 an hour. 
</P>
<P>
 The hourly fee includes use of the steel gazebo and the group picnic area. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the hourly fee, pavilion users must give the city a refundable 
deposit, based on the number of people expected to attend the event. The 
deposit is $50 for groups of up to 50 people, $100 for groups of 51 to 100 
people, and $150 for groups larger than 100. BILL BILLITER 
</P>
