COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: PLACENTIA; FUNDS FOR SOCCER PROGRAM DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A request for $2,000 to buy soccer equipment for a gang diversion program is 
on hold while Placentia city officials figure out how the city can fund the 
program and recover the money from the federal government. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council on Tuesday postponed the request from Casa Placentia, a 
program that serves low-income families by offering activities for youngsters. 
</P>
<P>
 The 22 youths in the Casa Placentia soccer program are forced to play in Santa 
Ana, where equipment is available through a similar program, Casa Placentia 
director Mike Buelna told the council. 
</P>
<P>
 Casa Placentia is to get $2,000 in federal money granted last year under the 
federal Housing and Community Development Act, but the money trickles into 
cities through state and county disbursement programs. Because the county 
contracts are not ready yet, the money has not been released. HOLLY J. WAGNER 
