<TEXT>
<P>
 Takeovers Headed for Second-Biggest Year: U.S. corporate takeovers are headed 
for their second-highest annual level, based on the strength of mergers in 
telecommunications, media and medicine.The value of announced mergers and 
acquisitions in the first 10 months of 1994 totaled $284.4 billion, according 
to Securities Data Co., which tracks financial markets. The year's totals will 
probably surpass the $292.9 billion mark set in 1989, Securities Data said. A 
record of $335.8 billion was set in 1988. This year's 10-month results reflect 
a 40% jump from $203 billion recorded in the same period in 1993. 
