industrial motors, in taking no position on Rockwell International Corp.'s 
unsolicited tender offer, cited "many uncertainties and conditions" related to 
the $1.5-billion cash bid.Reliance also said it still supports its planned 
merger with General Signal Corp., even though that proposed stock swap is 
valued at $1.3 billion. Separately, Seal Beach-based Rockwell said the 
president of its Troy, Mich.-based auto parts group, Ronald L. Roudebush, 
resigned and that the group is being restructured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
