<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEALS: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BATES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Cable TV: Billionaire Paul Allen is making a large minority investment in 
C/Net: The Computer Network, a proposed cable channel on computers, on-line 
services, video games and interactive services. The network, which some 
describe as an MTV-style channel for cyberspace, is scheduled for launch in the 
first part of 1995, with an on-line service to start simultaneously.C/Net plans 
to provide entertainment programming and consumer information about interactive 
services. Allen's Vulcan Venture will have two seats out of an expected seven 
on the C/Net board. The channel was founded by Halsey Minor, who previously 
founded a computer-oriented publishing company, and Kevin Wendle, a former Fox 
Entertainment executive vice president. Allen made his fortune founding 
computer software giant Microsoft with Bill Gates and has such investments as 
an 80% stake in Ticketmaster. The amount of his C/Net investment was not 
disclosed. JAMES BATES 
</P>
</TEXT>
